Definition at line 62 of file feeder_gmm.cpp.

#define FORCE_F_1_2_THRESH   0.05 /** Threshold between force regions 1 and 2*/

Refer to README.md for more info.

if force € [0, FORCE_F_1_2_THRESH] then state 1 : lower cup if force € (FORCE_F_1_2_THRESH, FORCE_F_2_3_THRESH] then state 2 : do nothing if force € (FORCE_F_2_3_THRESH, MAX] then state 3 : raise cup

Fallback velocity functions Vel.x Vel.y -180 to -90 y = 0.004444444*x + 0.8 -180 to 0 y = 0.004444444*x + 0.4 -90 to 90 y = -0.004444444*x 0 to 180 y = -0.004444444*x + 0.4 90 to 180 y = 0.004444444*x - 0.8

Definition at line 962 of file feeder_gmm.cpp.

void driveToRollGoalWithVelocity ( int  direction)

Wrapper for the actual targeted velocity controller. Manipulated Roll angle only.

Parameters
direction.Movement pattern requested.

Patterns supported by this controller

Calculate first the quaternion for how much roll angle to change

Multiply starting quat with the rotation quat to get the resultant goal quat

Convert the resultant quat to msg type

The proportional controller

Rescale from -180 to 180 into 0 to 360

Manipulate gripper until goal pose is reached or safety breach

Definition at line 359 of file feeder_gmm.cpp.

void fallback ( bool  emerg = false)

Wrapper for the fallback sequence.

fallback. Main fallback function.

fallback. The actual fallback function.

Parameters
emerg.Is it an emergency fallback or a timed fallback. Movement differs based on this.

Does not require a complicated trajectory calculation since the typical orientation for sideways feeding is fixed and fallback is always in the same direction.

Parameters
emerg.Also lower cup if emrgency to avoid spillage.

Actual trajectory depends on current orientation of the gripper.

Parameters
emerg

Fallback is position controller based, so it is in world coordinates. Calculate the approximate trajectory in world coordinates based in current pose. These calculations were made separately by hand. Because fallback has to always happen AWAY from the users face

Fallback velocity functions Vel.x Vel.y -180 to -90 y = 0.004444444*x + 0.8 -180 to 0 y = 0.004444444*x + 0.4 -90 to 90 y = -0.004444444*x 0 to 180 y = -0.004444444*x + 0.4 90 to 180 y = 0.004444444*x - 0.8

getNewPoseAtIndex. Calculate the new pose target for the current state

Take the actual starting pose from current run, consider the index of the GMR trajectory required, add the delta to take the starting pose to new index

new_index_in_trajectory.The index in the trajectory corresponds to the current poisiton of the arm. Not analogous to the Markov model state.
